solution_code: public class Solution {--newline--        public List<Integer> majorityElement(int[] nums) {--newline--        if (nums == null || nums.length == 0)--newline--            return new ArrayList<Integer>();--newline--        List<Integer> result = new ArrayList<Integer>();--newline--        int number1 = nums[0], number2 = nums[0], count1 = 0, count2 = 0, len = nums.length;--newline--        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {--newline--            if (nums[i] == number1)--newline--                count1++;--newline--            else if (nums[i] == number2)--newline--                count2++;--newline--            else if (count1 == 0) {--newline--                number1 = nums[i];--newline--                count1 = 1;--newline--            } else if (count2 == 0) {--newline--                number2 = nums[i];--newline--                count2 = 1;--newline--            } else {--newline--                count1--;--newline--                count2--;--newline--            }--newline--        }--newline--        count1 = 0;--newline--        count2 = 0;--newline--        for (int i = 0; i < len; i++) {--newline--            if (nums[i] == number1)--newline--                count1++;--newline--            else if (nums[i] == number2)--newline--                count2++;--newline--        }--newline--        if (count1 > len / 3)--newline--            result.add(number1);--newline--        if (count2 > len / 3)--newline--            result.add(number2);--newline--        return result;--newline--    }--newline--}
